In its continued  effort to tame corruption, economic and financial crimes in Nigeria, the  Kano Operational Zone of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission,  hosted the compliance officers of the four major GSM Service Providers  in Nigeria in its Zonal Office in Kano today. The Service
Providers comprising MTN, Glo, Airtel and 9 Mobile met with principal
officers of the zone for a smoother relationship between the EFCC and
their various Telecom Industries operations. Speaking at the event, Zonal Head of the EFCC’s Kano Office, Akaninyene
Ezima who represented the acting Chairman of the Commission, Ibrahim
Magu, urged the Compliance Officers to enhance their response levels to
the Commission’s letters and requests, while further soliciting their
support in the fight against corruption and cyber crimes. In
response, Abubakar Zubairu, MTN, on behalf of other service providers
assured the Commission of their unflinching support and building on the
existing relationship between the two bodies. Currently in Social Media platform of NTA, Largest TV in Africa. Iam a graduate of Mass Communication with special interest on social media and Online Editor and a Reporter.